\section software Software Management


\subsection downloading Downloading

The Acro software can be downloaded as a compressed tarfile from
<a href="http://software.sandia.gov/Acro/">http://software.sandia.gov/Acro/</a>.

Alternatively, Acro can be checked out from the Acro CVS (Concurrent Version System) repository. 
The CVS respository for Acro can be accessed by executing
\verbatim
    cvs -d :ext:${userid}@software.sandia.gov:/space/CVS-Acro checkout acro
\endverbatim
This requires the use of an account (userid) on \b software.sandia.gov.
Accounts on this machine are generally restricted to Sandians
and academic collaborators working with Sandians.  The scripts
\b cvs.a and \b ssh.cvs can be used to encapsulate the access to this
repository in a convenient manner; these scripts can be downloaded from <a
href="ftp://ftp.cs.sandia.gov/pub/papers/wehart/src/shells">ftp://ftp.cs.sandia.gov/pub/papers/wehart/src/shells</a>.

By default,  the \b cvs.a script uses the unix command \b whoami to determine
the user id for the cvs connection.  In general, the id ${userid} on software.sandia.gov will be selected by Sandia administrators.  If this does not match 
your id provided by \b whoami, then you can set the \b ACRO_USER environmental
variable to be id on software.sandia.gov.  For example, within a csh environment, you would do
\verbatim
   setenv ACRO_USER janedoe
   cvs.a checkout acro
\endverbatim
to checkout Acro from the account janedoe@software.sandia.gov.

The Acro CVS repository is organized into different modules that include different subsets of the
Acro packages:
